article.description: Justyna Podziemska had 19 points and 11 rebounds to lead Wyoming (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) to an 87-39 rout of UNLV.
article.headline: Podziemska's double-double powers Cowgirls over Rebels
article.linkText: Wyoming tops UNLV, stays perfect  in conference
article.story:
LARAMIE, Wyo. (AP) -- Justyna Podziemska had 19 points and 11 rebounds to lead Wyoming (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) to an 87-39 rout of UNLV on Wednesday night.

Aubrey Vandiver added 15 points and 10 rebounds for the Cowgirls (17-1, 5-0 Mountain West). Paula Elum came off the bench to score 11 points.

Podziemska's 3-pointer with 3:52 remaining in the first half capped an 18-4 run that gave Wyoming a 27-9 lead. She hit four more 3-pointers during a 29-7 run early in the second half to put the game out of reach.

The Cowgirls outrebounded UNLV (6-11, 2-2) 52-34 while holding the Lady Rebels to just 21 percent shooting. Wyoming also outscored UNLV 44-8 in bench points and finished with 19 more points off turnovers.

Shamela Hampton led UNLV with 10 points.
